# Backend API integration

Base URL: `import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL` (e.g. `http://localhost:8000/api`).

## Authentication

1. Login: redirect to `{API}/auth/google` (full page) **or** OAuth popup + `POST /auth/google/callback` with `{ code, state }`
2. After login: `sessionid` cookie (HttpOnly) — all requests use `credentials: 'include'`
3. Current user: `GET /auth/me`
4. Logout: `POST /auth/logout` (+ CSRF header)

## CSRF (required for POST, PATCH, PUT, DELETE)

```typescript
async function getCsrfToken(): Promise<string> {
  const res = await fetch(`${API}/auth/csrf`, { credentials: 'include' });
  const { csrfToken } = await res.json();
  return csrfToken;
}

async function apiFetch(path: string, init: RequestInit = {}) {
  const method = (init.method ?? 'GET').toUpperCase();
  const headers = new Headers(init.headers);
  if (['POST', 'PATCH', 'PUT', 'DELETE'].includes(method)) {
    headers.set('X-CSRFToken', await getCsrfToken());
  }
  if (init.body && !headers.has('Content-Type')) {
    headers.set('Content-Type', 'application/json');
  }
  return fetch(`${API}${path}`, { ...init, headers, credentials: 'include' });
}
```

## Error format

All errors: `{ error: { code, message, details } }`

| HTTP | Typical `code` |
|------|----------------|
| 400 | `VALIDATION_ERROR` |
| 403 | `FORBIDDEN` (not logged in) |
| 404 | `NOT_FOUND` |
| 409 | conflict (duplicate flight) |
| 429 | `THROTTLED` |
| 502 | `GOOGLE_API_ERROR` |

Parse `error.message` for user-facing text; use `details` for field errors.

## Logbook gate

Many endpoints return 400 if no logbook: connect via `POST /logbook/connect` first (`spreadsheet_id` or `url`).

## Flight ID in URLs

Composite ID (no slashes): e.g. `2025-11-08Field09:05Field10:15` — encode for URL path segment.
